Adjust rack to upper position and preheat oven to 425 degrees. Wash and dry all produce. Halve @Baby Red Potatoes{12%ounce}. Pick @Rosemary{¼%ounce} leaves from stems; mince leaves until you have ½ TBSP. Mince or grate @Garlic{2%clove}. Trim @Green Beans{6%ounce}. In a #small bowl{}, combine @Beef Stock Concentrate{1}, @Ketchup{2%tablespoon}, @Dijon Mustard{2%teaspoon}, 3 TBSP water, @Sugar{¼%teaspoon}, and @Hot Sauce{1%teaspoon} (to taste).

Toss potatoes in a #medium bowl{} with a drizzle of @Vegetable Oil{4%teaspoon}, minced rosemary, and a large pinch of @Salt{} and @Pepper{}. Arrange cut sides down on a lightly oiled #baking sheet{}. Roast until browned and tender, ~{25-30%minutes}.

Melt ½ TBSP @Butter{1.5%tablespoon} in a large pan over medium-high heat. Add garlic and cook until fragrant, about ~{30%seconds}. Add @Panko Breadcrumbs{¼%cup} and cook, stirring constantly, until golden brown, ~{3-5%minutes}. Season with salt and pepper. Remove from pan and set aside. Wipe out pan.

Pat @Sirloin Steak{10%ounce} dry with #paper towels{}; season all over with salt and pepper. Heat a large drizzle of oil in same pan over medium-high heat. Add steak and cook to desired doneness, ~{4-7%minutes} per side. Remove from pan, tent with #foil{}, and let rest until ready to serve. Reduce heat to low. Stir in sauce until thoroughly combined. Remove pan from heat; season with pepper.

While steak cooks, place green beans in a #medium microwave-safe bowl{} with a splash of water. Cover bowl with #plastic wrap{} and poke a few holes in wrap. Microwave on high until tender, ~{2-3%minutes}. Remove from microwave, drain water, then toss beans with 1 TBSP butter. Season with salt and pepper. Toss with garlic panko.

Divide steak, potatoes, and green beans between #plates{}. Top steak with sauce.